{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CqUoa7vZFbsR9bERghtqNj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nImplemented base image change detection in `internal/adapters/docker/build.go`:\n\n1. **`baseImageFromDockerfile(content []byte) string`** — Parses the last `FROM` directive from Dockerfile content, handling multi-stage builds, comments, and case-insensitive `FROM`.\n\n2. **`imageID(ctx, image) (string, error)`** — Runs `docker inspect --format '{{.Id}}'` to get the current base image ID.\n\n3. **`EnsureImage()` extended** — After the Dockerfile hash matches, it now also checks if the base image has changed by comparing the current base image ID against the stored `cloche.base.image.id` label. If the base image can't be inspected (not pulled yet), the check is skipped gracefully.\n\n4. **`buildImage()` extended** — Now stores the `cloche.base.image.id` label alongside `cloche.dockerfile.hash` during builds.\n\nTests added in `build_test.go`:\n- `TestBaseImageFromDockerfile` — 8 sub-cases covering single FROM, multi-stage, AS alias, comments, ARG before FROM, empty content, case insensitivity\n- `TestImageID_NonexistentImage` — verifies error on missing image\n- `TestEnsureImage_RebuildsWhenBaseImageChanges` — full integration test that builds a base image, builds a project image, rebuilds the base, and verifies staleness detection\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":355,"cache_read_input_tokens":29377,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":355},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e2002079-b665-4375-893a-6251b75ea2c2","uuid":"57759670-1943-47ed-a8cf-28876ca75a99"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":132059,"duration_api_ms":107811,"num_turns":19,"result":"## Summary\n\nImplemented base image change detection in `internal/adapters/docker/build.go`:\n\n1. **`baseImageFromDockerfile(content []byte) string`** — Parses the last `FROM` directive from Dockerfile content, handling multi-stage builds, comments, and case-insensitive `FROM`.\n\n2. **`imageID(ctx, image) (string, error)`** — Runs `docker inspect --format '{{.Id}}'` to get the current base image ID.\n\n3. **`EnsureImage()` extended** — After the Dockerfile hash matches, it now also checks if the base image has changed by comparing the current base image ID against the stored `cloche.base.image.id` label. If the base image can't be inspected (not pulled yet), the check is skipped gracefully.\n\n4. **`buildImage()` extended** — Now stores the `cloche.base.image.id` label alongside `cloche.dockerfile.hash` during builds.\n\nTests added in `build_test.go`:\n- `TestBaseImageFromDockerfile` — 8 sub-cases covering single FROM, multi-stage, AS alias, comments, ARG before FROM, empty content, case insensitivity\n- `TestImageID_NonexistentImage` — verifies error on missing image\n- `TestEnsureImage_RebuildsWhenBaseImageChanges` — full integration test that builds a base image, builds a project image, rebuilds the base, and verifies staleness detection\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"e2002079-b665-4375-893a-6251b75ea2c2","total_cost_usd":0.49367825,"usage":{"input_tokens":21,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24481,"cache_read_input_tokens":368234,"output_tokens":6258,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":24481,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":21,"outputTokens":6258,"cacheReadInputTokens":368234,"cacheCreationInputTokens":2448